commits.message:
build: provide a separate version script for each module

GNU ld with --no-undefined-version option issues a warning for each
undefined symbol mentioned in the version script, and --fatal-warnings
option turns such warnings into errors.  Other linkers, e.g. lld and
mold, have --no-undefined-version option enabled by default.

Given that different modules export different set of pam_sm_* symbols,
the only way of resolving this issue without turning
--no-undefined-version and --fatal-warnings options off is to provide
a separate version script for each module.

To avoid potential regressions in the future, this change also adds
--no-undefined-version option to the linker.

Resolves: https://github.com/linux-pam/linux-pam/issues/922

issue.title: Container images for CI and Performance builds
issue.body:
Since the CI builds need different tools to be available (python, go, rust,...), we should create images and store it on ghcr to be used by the workflows. We should build the images at the beginning  of the workflow run, to have it available, when other jobs run and need them.
The detect-changes job should trigger these container builds, if needed and if not needed, the following steps shall use the latest image.

pull_request.title: Feat: Add User Authorization Callback
pull_request.body:
This pull request introduces a user authorization mechanism using an ADK `before_agent_callback`. 

Key changes:
- A new `check_user_authorization` callback function has been added to `personal_clone/agent.py`.
- This function checks the `user_id` from the session against a hardcoded list of `AUTHORIZED_USER_IDS`.
- If the user is not in the list, agent execution is halted, and an 'Access Denied' message is returned.
- The callback has been added to the `before_agent_callback` list in the `create_master_agent` function, ensuring it runs before any other agent logic.

pull_request.title: Bump github.com/redis/go-redis/v9 from 9.12.0 to 9.12.1
pull_request.body:
Bumps [github.com/redis/go-redis/v9](https://github.com/redis/go-redis) from 9.12.0 to 9.12.1.
Release notes

Sourced from github.com/redis/go-redis/v9's releases.

9.12.1

üöÄ Highlights

In the last version (9.12.0) the client introduced bigger write and read buffer sizes. The default value was 512KiB. However, users reported that this is too big for most use cases and can lead to high memory usage. In this version the default value is changed to 256KiB. The README.md was updated to reflect the correct default value and include a note that the default value can be changed.

üêõ Bug Fixes

  • fix(options): Add buffer sizes to failover. Update README (#3468)

üß∞ Maintenance

  • fix(options): Add buffer sizes to failover. Update README (#3468)
  • chore: update & fix otel example (#3466)

Contributors

We'd like to thank all the contributors who worked on this release!

@‚Äãndyakov and @‚Äãvmihailenco

Changelog

Sourced from github.com/redis/go-redis/v9's changelog.

9.12.1 (2025-08-11)

üöÄ Highlights

In the last version (9.12.0) the client introduced bigger write and read buffer sized. The default value we set was 512KiB. However, users reported that this is too big for most use cases and can lead to high memory usage. In this version the default value is changed to 256KiB. The README.md was updated to reflect the correct default value and include a note that the default value can be changed.

üêõ Bug Fixes

  • fix(options): Add buffer sizes to failover. Update README (#3468)

üß∞ Maintenance
